## PART I: LAYER v6.0.1 — LAPTOP & INCOME GENERATION

### CATEGORY 8: LAPTOP / DIGITAL INFRASTRUCTURE ACQUISITION

#### **Task 8.1 — Free Geek Portland (Refurbished Devices)**

**Organization:** Free Geek (Portland Nonprofit)  
**Service:** Low-cost and free refurbished computers, phones, monitors  
**Location:** 1731 SE 10th Avenue, Portland, OR 97214  
**Contact:** (503) 232-9350 | freegeek.org  
**Cost Range:** $0–$100 (refurbished laptops typically $20–$80)  
**Timeline:** 1–2 weeks (pop-up shops monthly; online store immediate)  
**Requirements:** Minimal documentation; priority to justice-involved individuals  

**Why This Works:**
- On-site functionality verification (test device before leaving)
- Explicit mission alignment with reentry communities
- Multiple access channels (pop-ups, online store, thrift)
- ~10,000 devices refurbished annually (robust inventory)

**Action Steps:**
1. Visit freegeek.org for pop-up event schedule (typically 1st Saturday monthly, 11 AM–4 PM)
2. Browse online inventory at e-store.freegeek.org
3. Select laptop with specs: Intel i5+, 8GB RAM ideal (i3, 4GB acceptable for freelancing)
4. Purchase on-site or online with free local pickup
5. Test immediately; request refund/exchange guarantee if unmet

**Priority Index:** 9.2/10

---

#### **Task 8.2 — PCs for People (Subsidized Laptop + Internet Bundle)**

**Organization:** PCs for People (National Nonprofit)  
**Service:** Subsidized refurbished computers + ultra-low-cost internet (5G LTE $15–$35/month, no credit check)  
**Coverage:** Oregon supported  
**Contact:** pcsforpeople.org  
**Cost:** $50–$150 laptop + $15–$35/month internet  
**Timeline:** 2–4 weeks  
**Requirements:** Income verification (reentry status aids eligibility)  

**Bundled Value:** Solves dual bottleneck (device + connectivity)

**Action Steps:**
1. Visit pcsforpeople.org; verify Oregon service area
2. Gather income documentation (reentry support letters helpful)
3. Complete online application
4. Choose refurbished model + internet plan tier
5. Receive device within 3–4 weeks; activate internet simultaneously

**Priority Index:** 8.8/10

---

#### **Task 8.3 — Computers with Causes (Free Refurbished Computer Program)**

**Organization:** Computers with Causes (National)  
**Service:** Free refurbished computers to individuals in need  
**Cost:** FREE  
**Application:** Mail-in form  
**Timeline:** 30 days typical response  
**Requirements:** Completed application, need assessment, reference check  

**Use Case:** Parallel application (backup if Free Geek/PCs for People exceed 30 days)

**Action Steps:**
1. Download application at computerswithcauses.org/application
2. Complete form (mention post-incarceration reentry + freelance/education goals)
3. Provide reference (probation officer, case manager, or employer)
4. Mail to address provided
5. Await approval (30-day window)

**Priority Index:** 8.5/10

---

#### **Task 8.4 — WorkSource Oregon Reentry Program (Comprehensive Pre/Post-Release)**

**Organization:** Oregon Workforce Partnership + East Cascades Works  
**Service:** Computer lab access, job coaching, tech training, equipment subsidies (up to $6,000)  
**Availability:** All 12 Oregon prisons + statewide post-release services  
**Cost:** FREE (federally funded)  
**Eligibility:** Recent/upcoming release from Oregon state prison; 900 participants/year (~13% of releases)  

**Why This Is Strategic:**
- Integrated ecosystem: housing + employment + tech + education
- Equipment subsidy up to $6,000/participant (covers laptop + software)
- Computer labs at every prison + community centers
- Case management continuity (prison → community)

**Action Steps:**
1. **If still incarcerated (90–270 days pre-release):** Request enrollment through institutional education coordinator
2. **If recently released:** Contact East Cascades Works or local LWDB
3. Upon enrollment: Assign case manager + create individual employment plan
4. Access computer labs for skill-building
5. Request equipment subsidy as part of employment plan (document laptop/software as job requirement)
6. Receive job placement coaching + employer connections

**Verified Outcomes:** 995+ enrolled since July 2024; average $6,000 equipment/training support per participant

**Priority Index:** 9.5/10

