#### **Income Tier 2: Specialized (Music & Code)**

**Task 9.4 — SoundBetter Music Production Marketplace**

**Platform:** Dedicated music production freelance network  
**Device Access:** Smartphone for browsing; desktop for delivery  
**Cost:** Free (platform percentage on service rate)  
**Gig Types:** Mixing, mastering, production, beat production, vocal engineering  
**Time to First Earnings:** 3–7 days (if portfolio strong)  

**Earning Range (per-project):**
- Mixing: $300–$2,000 per song
- Mastering: $50–$500 per track
- Beat production: $50–$500 per beat
- Full production: $500–$5,000+

**Action Plan:**
1. Create SoundBetter account (free)
2. Upload 3–5 best production samples (SoundCloud links or direct audio)
3. Write compelling service description
4. Apply to 3–5 projects matching skill level
5. Deliver excellently; request detailed review
6. Once 5+ positive reviews: Raise rates 30–50%
7. Monitor marketplace for sync opportunities

**Priority Index:** 9.1/10

---

**Task 9.5 — Music Distribution (RouteNote/DistroKid) — Streaming Royalties**

**Platform:** Digital music distribution to Spotify, Apple Music, TikTok, 150+ stores  
**Device Access:** Desktop for uploads; smartphone for tracking  
**Cost:** FREE (RouteNote 85% royalties) or $9.99–$39.99/year (DistroKid/TuneCore)  
**Income Type:** Streaming royalties ($0.003–$0.005/stream) + sync licensing  

**Prerequisites:**
- 3–5 production-ready tracks (mastered, artwork completed)
- Metadata (artist name, track titles, tags)
- Artwork (1400×1400px, PNG/JPG)

**Action Plan:**
1. Finalize 3–5 instrumental/background music tracks (32-bit WAV or MP3, mastered)
2. Create professional artwork (use Canva free tier if needed)
3. Register with RouteNote (free)
4. Upload tracks with complete metadata:
   - Artist name, track title, album name
   - Genre, mood tags (critical for discovery)
   - Year of creation
   - ISRC auto-generated; UPC auto-assigned
5. Select "Distribute to all stores"
6. Tracks live within 7–14 days
7. Monitor monthly earnings via dashboard

**Realistic Income:** $20–$100/month per artist after 6 months

**Acceleration Tactic:** Promote via SoundCloud, Reddit, YouTube, Discord. Each share = potential playlist adds = compounding streams

**Priority Index:** 9.3/10

---

**Task 9.6 — Toptal Vetted Freelance Network (Premium Track)**

**Platform:** Exclusive "top 3%" freelancer network  
**Device Access:** Smartphone interface available; desktop preferred  
**Cost:** Free to apply; standard marketplace fees post-acceptance  
**Vetting:** Multi-stage (coding challenge, interview, portfolio review)  
**Rejection Rate:** 97% (challenging but worthwhile if accepted)  

**Earning Potential (if accepted):**
- Software developers: $50–$150/hour
- Music producers: $60–$120/hour
- UI/UX designers: $50–$100/hour

**Prerequisites for Strong Application:**
- Strong GitHub portfolio (if coder)
- Professional SoundCloud/portfolio (if music producer)
- 2+ years demonstrated experience (or exceptional portfolio quality)
- Willingness to undergo technical assessment

**Action Plan:**
1. Prepare portfolio materials (GitHub repos OR SoundCloud tracks OR design case studies)
2. Write compelling Toptal profile
3. Apply to Toptal (expect 2–4 week evaluation)
4. Complete vetting tasks honestly
5. **If rejected:** View feedback as learning; reapply in 6 months
6. **If accepted:** Apply to vetted project board; prioritize higher-rate clients

**Timeline to Employment:** Acceptance = 4–6 weeks; First project within 2–4 weeks post-acceptance

**Priority Index:** 8.3/10

