## PART II: LAYER v6.0.2 — CERTIFICATIONS, LICENSES & TRAINING

### TIER 1: FREE CERTIFICATIONS (100% NO-COST)

#### **Certification A.1 — ISC2 Certified in Cybersecurity (CC)**

**Program:** ISC2 "One Million Certifications" Initiative  
**Cost:** Completely free (training + exam)  
**What You Get:**
- FREE self-paced online training (100+ hours)
- FREE certification exam
- Annual membership: $50/year only (after certification)

**Why This Matters:** Cybersecurity entry-level roles: $60K–$85K nationally. Zero experience requirement—training included. Legitimate tier-one credential.

**Eligibility:** Reentry-friendly; anyone 18+ can apply

**Action Plan:**
1. Visit isc2.org and complete candidate application
2. Select "Certified in Cybersecurity (CC)"
3. Enroll in FREE Official ISC2 CC Online Self-Paced Training
4. Complete training modules (8–12 weeks at 10 hrs/week)
5. Schedule exam through Pearson VUE (free voucher after training)
6. Pass exam (60% passing score)
7. Pay $50 AMF (annual maintenance fee) to activate certification

**Career Bridge:** Cybersecurity fundamentals → CompTIA Security+ → CISSP

**Priority Index:** 9.5/10

---

#### **Certification A.2 — freeCodeCamp Web Development Certifications (11 Total)**

**Platform:** freeCodeCamp.org  
**Cost:** $0 (all courses + exams free and open-source)  

**11 Certifications Available:**
1. Responsive Web Design (HTML, CSS, Flexbox, CSS Grid)
2. JavaScript Algorithms and Data Structures
3. Front End Development Libraries (React, Redux, Bootstrap)
4. Data Visualization (D3.js)
5. Back End Development and APIs (Node.js, Express)
6. Quality Assurance (testing frameworks)
7. Information Security (penetration testing basics)
8. Relational Database (SQL)
9. Python for Beginners
10. Machine Learning with Python
11. College Algebra (foundational math)

**Why This Works:** 100% free; 5 major projects per certification; verified open-source exams; shareable certificates; builds working portfolio

**Timeline:** 300+ hours each (2–4 months part-time)

**Strategic Sequence:**
1. Weeks 1–4: Responsive Web Design
2. Weeks 5–8: JavaScript Algorithms
3. Weeks 9–12: Front End Development Libraries (React)
4. Weeks 13–16: Back End APIs
5. Weeks 17–20: Data Visualization or QA

**Execution:**
1. Create free freeCodeCamp account
2. Select certification path
3. Work through interactive lessons + labs + projects
4. Complete 5 required certification projects
5. Take 50-question exam
6. Download shareable certificate

**Portfolio Outcome:** By month 6–8: 3–4 certifications + 12–15 real projects on GitHub = hireable for junior developer roles ($50K–$70K)

**Priority Index:** 9.4/10

---

