### TIER 3: SPECIALIZED CODING & TECH TRAINING (GAME-CHANGING)

#### **Training C.1 — Next Chapter Project (PAID Apprenticeship + Transformed Career)**

**Program:** Next Chapter (formerly incarcerated software engineer pathway)  
**Eligibility:** Formerly incarcerated individuals ONLY  
**Cost:** PAID apprenticeship (you receive salary during training)  
**Duration:** 8 months total
- 3 months: Intermediate Coding Bootcamp (Hack Reactor)
- 5 months: Paid apprenticeship at tech company

**What You Receive:**
- **Salary during entire training** ($50K–$70K annualized)
- Advanced coding bootcamp enrollment (normally $15K–$20K value)
- One-on-one mentorship from software engineers
- Job placement at leading tech company
- **Average starting salary after graduation: $100K+/year**

**Success Metrics (Verified):**
- 92% placement rate into full-time software engineer roles
- 0% recidivism rate (no alumni returned to incarceration)
- 15+ alumni promoted beyond Associate Software Engineer
- All alumni thriving in the free world

**Curriculum:**
- JavaScript, React, Node.js, system design
- Full-stack web application development
- Team collaboration + professional communication
- Code review + industry best practices

**Why This Is Transformational:** Only 8-month pathway from zero coding experience → $100K tech job. Designed BY + FOR formerly incarcerated individuals. Zero recidivism.

**Companies Hiring:** Slack, Salesforce, Twitter, Twilio, Affirm

**Application Timeline:**
- Applications open: Varies (check nextchapterproject.org quarterly)
- Selection process: 4–8 weeks
- Program start: Typically quarterly cohorts
- Time to employment: 8 months

**Action Plan:**
1. Visit nextchapterproject.org
2. Check current application status (open/closed)
3. If open: Complete application form
4. Prepare for technical screening (logic/problem-solving)
5. Undergo interviews (behavior + motivation)
6. If selected: Begin 3-month Hack Reactor bootcamp
7. Complete coding projects + capstone
8. Transition to 5-month paid apprenticeship
9. Upon completion: Full-time offer

**Strategic Value:** Highest-ROI reentry program nationally. Eliminates need for many other training paths. $100K starting salary after 8 months is unmatched.

**Priority Index:** 9.8/10

---

#### **Training C.2 — WeReach Reentry Workforce Development (IT Track)**

**Program:** WeReach Re-entry Workforce Development Program  
**Eligibility:** Formerly incarcerated or justice-involved individuals  
**Cost:** FREE  
**Duration:** 6–12 months (self-paced)  

**Main Track: IT Training (Cybersecurity + IT Services)**
- Specialized training: Cybersecurity support, IT services, networking
- Sequential courses (build on prior)
- Certificate per completed course
- Tailored for reentry (trauma-informed, culturally responsive)

**Services Included:**
- Career coaching (during + after)
- Job placement assistance
- Peer support community
- Ongoing career development

**Why This Approach:** Programs designed BY + FOR returning citizens have fundamentally different effectiveness than generic bootcamps. WeReach understood that justice-involved individuals need trauma-informed instruction + community support.

**Timeline:**
- Initial inquiry: Submit form at wereach.us
- Intake call: 1–2 weeks
- Course start: 2–4 weeks after intake
- Pace: Self-directed (5–10 hrs/week typical)

**Action Plan:**
1. Visit wereach.us/a-inside-programs
2. Complete inquiry form (basic info + IT interest)
3. Expect follow-up within 1–2 weeks
4. Discuss experience level + schedule
5. Enroll in first course (IT fundamentals)
6. Complete first certification (4–8 weeks)
7. Progress to next course
8. Upon 3+ courses: Eligible for job placement support
9. Receive career coaching + employer introductions

**Differentiation:** Justice-involved specific; peer support + community; counseling + wraparound; real pathway to sustainable employment

**Priority Index:** 8.8/10

---

